The paper deals with the problem of partial person re-identification, which involves matching partial observations of persons. This problem is closely related to computer vision and machine learning, which are covered by the cs.CV and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel method called Deep Spatial feature Reconstruction (DSR), which involves dictionary learning models and similarity calculations, indicating a potential fit with the cs.MM and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves image matching and similarity calculations, which are also relevant to the cs.IR sub-category.
